Hi Emma and William,
<br/>
			
<br/>
			Milan is such a cool place!
<br/>
			We've arrived and the hotel is great! It's warm here, and we're going to meet Maria and her mum and dad for lunch.
<br/>
			After that we're going to climb the cathedral – they say the view of Milan is amazing from there!
<br/>
			Mum and Dad want to see the Leonardo da Vinci paintings, but the museum will be really busy and maybe they won't get tickets. While they're at the museum, I'm going to the Euro Luna Park with Maria. It's a huge amusement park.
<br/>
			Tomorrow's going to be great too – we're going to travel out to see Lake Como – they say it's really beautiful and the weather will be fine, so we can hire boats. Then we're going to visit this really famous ice cream house and we're going to eat lots of ice cream!
<br/>
			Then, on Monday, we'll stay in Milan and go shopping. We want to see all the big fashion houses! Of course, I won't have any money to buy anything, but it'll be nice to see any clothes.
<br/>
			My Italian is getting better!
<br/>
			How are you two? 
<br/>
			
<br/>
			Lots of love, 
<br/>
			Kate</simpleText>
